		<p class="case-study__regular">
			<b>Yoga para Mí</b> is a collection of online Yoga lessons and meditation guides for Hispanic audiences. We helped Yoga para Mi to redesign their online fitness platform, bringing their top-quality video lessons to a wider online audience.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="imagery-block" style="background-image: url(https://s3.amazonaws.com/icalialabs/assets/img/yoga/imagery.png)"></div>

	<div class="smaller-container">
		<h6 class="case-study__title">THE CHALLENGE</h6>
		<h2 class="case-study__question">How to get more users past the signup process and into <span>getting paid subscriptions</span>?</h2>
		<p class="case-study__content">
			Yoga para Mi’s founders had previously created an online platform to host their videos, but the platform wasn’t working quite well due to a poor implementation. They were afraid that they were losing customers because of this, and requested a full redesign from us.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="imagery-block" style="background-image: url(https://s3.amazonaws.com/icalialabs/assets/img/yoga/01-sprint.png)"></div>

	<div class="smaller-container">
		<h6 class="case-study__title">OUR APPROACH</h6>
		<p class="case-study__regular">
			A quick customer research exercise showed us that their current users loved the quality of the videos (produced by an inner team with high standards); and the reputation of their instructors was attracting new customers to the platform. However, retention rates remained below 10% during the first year of operation.
		</p>
		<p class="case-study__regular">
			The biggest barrier was signing up and paying a membership – a bad user interface and sloppy implementation led to a poor user experience. With that in mind, <span>we decided to enhance the onboarding experience, as well as lifting up the editorial and visual experience throughout all the experience.</span>
	</div>

